<subSubSection pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="51.[151,1436,222,571]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,367,391]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
There are several records of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1867" box="[643,808,366,390]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Macrophthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandidieri">
<emphasis box="[643,666,367,390]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[681,808,366,390]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">grandidieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Persian Gulf [
<bibRefCitation author="Basson, P. W. &amp; Burchard, J. E. &amp; Hardy, J. T. &amp; Price, A. R. G." box="[1074,1303,366,390]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refId="ref45702" refString="Basson, P. W., Burchard, J. E., Hardy, J. T. &amp; Price, A. R. G. (1977) Biotopes of the Western Arabian Gulf: Marine life and environments of Saudi Arabia. ARAMCO, Dept. of Loss Prevention and environmental affairs, Dhahran: 289 pp." type="book" year="1977">
Basson 
<emphasis box="[1165,1214,366,390]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">et al</emphasis>
. (1977)
</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry name="Saudi Arabia" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Saudi Arabia</collectingCountry>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Clayton, D. A." box="[247,422,402,426]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="83 - 96" refId="ref46310" refString="Clayton, D. A. (1986) Ecology of mudflats with particular reference to those of the northern Arabian Gulf. In: Halwagy, R., D. Clayton, &amp; M. Behbehani (eds.), Marine Environment and Pollution. Proceedings of the 1 st Persian Gulf Conference on Environment and Pollution, Kuwait, 7 - 9 February 1982. University of Kuwait, 83 - 96." type="proceedings paper" year="1986">Clayton (1986)</bibRefCitation>
and Jones (1986) from 
<collectingCountry box="[714,800,402,426]" name="Kuwait" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Kuwait</collectingCountry>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Vousden, D. H." box="[817,999,402,426]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refId="ref53448" refString="Vousden, D. H. (1987) The Bahrain Marine Habitat Survey. A study of the marine habitats in the waters of Bahrain and their relationship to physical, chemical, biological and anthropogenic influences. Published by: R. O. P. M. E. (Kuwait), 95 pp. + Appendices." type="book" year="1987">Vousden (1987)</bibRefCitation>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1078,1169,402,426]" name="Bahrain" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Bahrain</collectingCountry>
] that are misidentified specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="H. Milne Edwards" authorityYear="1852" box="[312,444,438,462]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Macrophthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulcatus">
<emphasis box="[312,335,439,462]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[352,444,438,462]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">sulcatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see 
<bibRefCitation author="Apel, M. &amp; Turkay, M." box="[510,757,438,462]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" pagination="131 - 142" refId="ref45263" refString="Apel, M., &amp; Turkay, M. (1999) Taxonomic Composition, Distribution and Zoogeographic Relationships of the Grapsid and Ocypodid Crab Fauna of Intertidal Soft Bottoms in the Persian Gulf. Estuarine, Coastal and Shelf Science, 49 (Supplement A), 131 - 142" type="journal article" year="1999">Apel &amp; Türkay 1999</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Apel, M." box="[772,896,438,462]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" refId="ref45060" refString="Apel, M. (2001) Taxonomie und Zoogeographie der Brachyura, Paguridea und Porcellanidae (Crustacea: Decapoda) des Persisch-Arabischen Golfes. Unpublished doctoral thesis, Johann Wolfgang Goethe-Universitat, Frankfurt a. M., 268 pp." type="book" year="2001">Apel 2001</bibRefCitation>
; Naderloo 
<emphasis box="[1026,1079,438,462]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">et al</emphasis>
. 2011). Naderloo 
<emphasis box="[1292,1344,438,462]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">et al</emphasis>
. (2011) recorded 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A. Milne-Edwards" authorityYear="1867" box="[260,429,475,499]" class="Malacostraca" family="Macrophthalmidae" genus="Macrophthalmus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="grandidieri">
<emphasis box="[260,283,475,498]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[301,429,475,499]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">grandidieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the 
<specimenCount box="[598,752,474,498]" pageId="51" pageNumber="52" type="juvenile">two juveniles</specimenCount>
from the Persian Gulf, whereas this species looks to be a common species in the sandy substrate of the seaward fringe of mangroves in 
<collectingCountry box="[1036,1121,511,534]" name="Oman" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Muscat</collectingCountry>
, Gulf of 
<collectingCountry box="[1223,1291,510,534]" name="Oman" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">Oman</collectingCountry>
(see Hywel- Davies 1994; Naderloo 
<emphasis box="[417,466,547,571]" italics="true" pageId="51" pageNumber="52">et al</emphasis>
. 2011).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
